Note: Runa Standard Library - Symmetric Encryption Algorithms
This module provides production-grade symmetric encryption including AES, ChaCha20, 
DES/3DES (legacy), stream ciphers, and block cipher modes of operation.

Supports ECB, CBC, CFB, OFB, CTR, and GCM modes with proper initialization vector
handling, padding schemes, and security best practices for confidentiality.

Specification compliance: FIPS 197 (AES), RFC 7539 (ChaCha20), NIST SP 800-38A (Modes).
:End Note

Import "crypto/primitives/random" as random
Import "crypto/hash" as hash

Type SymmetricResult is Union with:
    SymmetricSuccess with value as Dictionary[String, Any]
    SymmetricFailure with error as SymmetricError and message as String

Type SymmetricError is Enum with:
    Invalid_Key_Size
    Invalid_Block_Size
    Invalid_IV_Size
    Invalid_Plaintext
    Invalid_Ciphertext
    Invalid_Mode
    Invalid_Padding
    Encryption_Failed
    Decryption_Failed
    Authentication_Failed
    Internal_Error

Type SymmetricAlgorithm is Enum with:
    AES_128
    AES_192
    AES_256
    ChaCha20
    XChaCha20
    DES
    TripleDES
    Blowfish
    Twofish

Type BlockCipherMode is Enum with:
    ECB
    CBC
    CFB
    OFB
    CTR
    GCM

Type PaddingScheme is Enum with:
    PKCS7
    ANSIX923
    ISO10126
    Zero_Padding
    No_Padding

Type SymmetricKey is Dictionary with:
    algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm
    key_data as List[Integer]
    key_size as Integer
    created_at as Integer

Type SymmetricCiphertext is Dictionary with:
    algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm
    mode as BlockCipherMode
    ciphertext as List[Integer]
    iv as List[Integer]
    tag as Optional[List[Integer]]
    padding as PaddingScheme
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type StreamCipherState is Dictionary with:
    algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm
    key as List[Integer]
    nonce as List[Integer]
    counter as Integer
    keystream_buffer as List[Integer]
    buffer_position as Integer

Note: Algorithm Constants
Let AES_BLOCK_SIZE be 16
Let DES_BLOCK_SIZE be 8
Let CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE be 32
Let CHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE be 12
Let XCHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE be 24
Let GCM_TAG_SIZE be 16
Let DEFAULT_KEY_SIZE be 32

Note: Primary Symmetric Encryption Interface

Process called "encrypt_symmetric" that takes plaintext as List[Integer] and key as SymmetricKey and algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm and mode as BlockCipherMode and padding as Optional[PaddingScheme] returns SymmetricResult[SymmetricCiphertext]:
    Note: Encrypt data using symmetric algorithm with specified mode
    Try:
        Note: Validate inputs
        If plaintext is None or (length of plaintext) is equal to 0:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Plaintext
                message as "Plaintext cannot be empty"
        
        If not is_valid_key_for_algorithm with key as key and algorithm as algorithm:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Key_Size
                message as "Invalid key size for algorithm"
        
        Note: Generate initialization vector
        Let iv_result be generate_iv_for_mode with algorithm as algorithm and mode as mode
        Match iv_result:
            When SymmetricFailure:
                Return iv_result
            When SymmetricSuccess with value as iv:
                Note: Apply padding if required
                Let padding_scheme be padding if padding is not None else PaddingScheme.PKCS7
                Let padded_plaintext_result be apply_padding with data as plaintext and algorithm as algorithm and mode as mode and padding as padding_scheme
                
                Match padded_plaintext_result:
                    When SymmetricFailure:
                        Return padded_plaintext_result
                    When SymmetricSuccess with value as padded_plaintext:
                        Note: Perform encryption based on algorithm and mode
                        Match algorithm:
                            When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_128:
                                Return encrypt_aes with plaintext as padded_plaintext and key as key.key_data and iv as iv and mode as mode
                            When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_192:
                                Return encrypt_aes with plaintext as padded_plaintext and key as key.key_data and iv as iv and mode as mode
                            When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_256:
                                Return encrypt_aes with plaintext as padded_plaintext and key as key.key_data and iv as iv and mode as mode
                            When SymmetricAlgorithm.ChaCha20:
                                Return encrypt_chacha20 with plaintext as padded_plaintext and key as key.key_data and nonce as iv
                            When SymmetricAlgorithm.XChaCha20:
                                Return encrypt_xchacha20 with plaintext as padded_plaintext and key as key.key_data and nonce as iv
                            When SymmetricAlgorithm.DES:
                                Return encrypt_des with plaintext as padded_plaintext and key as key.key_data and iv as iv and mode as mode
                            When SymmetricAlgorithm.TripleDES:
                                Return encrypt_3des with plaintext as padded_plaintext and key as key.key_data and iv as iv and mode as mode
                            Otherwise:
                                Return SymmetricFailure with:
                                    error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Mode
                                    message as "Unsupported algorithm: " plus (algorithm as String)
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
            message as "Symmetric encryption error: " plus error as String

Process called "decrypt_symmetric" that takes ciphertext as SymmetricCiphertext and key as SymmetricKey returns SymmetricResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Decrypt data using symmetric algorithm 
    Try:
        Note: Validate inputs
        If ciphertext.ciphertext is None or (length of ciphertext.ciphertext) is equal to 0:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Ciphertext
                message as "Ciphertext cannot be empty"
        
        If not is_valid_key_for_algorithm with key as key and algorithm as ciphertext.algorithm:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Key_Size
                message as "Invalid key size for algorithm"
        
        Note: Perform decryption based on algorithm and mode
        Let decryption_result be None
        Match ciphertext.algorithm:
            When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_128:
                Set decryption_result to decrypt_aes with ciphertext as ciphertext.ciphertext and key as key.key_data and iv as ciphertext.iv and mode as ciphertext.mode
            When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_192:
                Set decryption_result to decrypt_aes with ciphertext as ciphertext.ciphertext and key as key.key_data and iv as ciphertext.iv and mode as ciphertext.mode
            When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_256:
                Set decryption_result to decrypt_aes with ciphertext as ciphertext.ciphertext and key as key.key_data and iv as ciphertext.iv and mode as ciphertext.mode
            When SymmetricAlgorithm.ChaCha20:
                Set decryption_result to decrypt_chacha20 with ciphertext as ciphertext.ciphertext and key as key.key_data and nonce as ciphertext.iv
            When SymmetricAlgorithm.XChaCha20:
                Set decryption_result to decrypt_xchacha20 with ciphertext as ciphertext.ciphertext and key as key.key_data and nonce as ciphertext.iv
            When SymmetricAlgorithm.DES:
                Set decryption_result to decrypt_des with ciphertext as ciphertext.ciphertext and key as key.key_data and iv as ciphertext.iv and mode as ciphertext.mode
            When SymmetricAlgorithm.TripleDES:
                Set decryption_result to decrypt_3des with ciphertext as ciphertext.ciphertext and key as key.key_data and iv as ciphertext.iv and mode as ciphertext.mode
            Otherwise:
                Return SymmetricFailure with:
                    error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Mode
                    message as "Unsupported algorithm for decryption"
        
        Match decryption_result:
            When SymmetricFailure:
                Return decryption_result
            When SymmetricSuccess with value as padded_plaintext:
                Note: Remove padding
                Let unpadded_result be remove_padding with data as padded_plaintext and padding as ciphertext.padding
                Return unpadded_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
            message as "Symmetric decryption error: " plus error as String

Process called "generate_symmetric_key" that takes algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm returns SymmetricResult[SymmetricKey]:
    Note: Generate cryptographically secure symmetric key
    Try:
        Let key_size be get_key_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm
        If key_size is equal to 0:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Key_Size
                message as "Invalid algorithm or unsupported key size"
        
        Let key_result be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as key_size
        Match key_result:
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return SymmetricFailure with:
                    error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
                    message as "Failed to generate secure key"
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as key_data:
                Let symmetric_key be SymmetricKey with:
                    algorithm as algorithm
                    key_data as key_data
                    key_size as key_size
                    created_at as time.to_timestamp with datetime as time.now
                
                Return SymmetricSuccess with value as symmetric_key
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
            message as "Key generation error: " plus error as String

Note: AES Implementation

Process called "encrypt_aes" that takes plaintext as List[Integer] and key as List[Integer] and iv as List[Integer] and mode as BlockCipherMode returns SymmetricResult[SymmetricCiphertext]:
    Note: AES encryption with specified mode
    Try:
        Note: Validate AES parameters
        Let key_size be length of key
        If key_size is not equal to 16 and key_size is not equal to 24 and key_size is not equal to 32:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Key_Size
                message as "AES key must be 128, 192, or 256 bits"
        
        If (length of plaintext) modulo AES_BLOCK_SIZE is not equal to 0:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Block_Size
                message as "AES plaintext must be multiple of block size after padding"
        
        Note: Determine AES variant
        Let aes_algorithm be SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_128
        If key_size is equal to 24:
            Set aes_algorithm to SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_192
        Else If key_size is equal to 32:
            Set aes_algorithm to SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_256
        
        Note: Perform mode-specific encryption
        Match mode:
            When BlockCipherMode.ECB:
                Let ciphertext_result be aes_encrypt_ecb with plaintext as plaintext and key as key
                Match ciphertext_result:
                    When SymmetricSuccess with value as ciphertext_data:
                        Let result be SymmetricCiphertext with:
                            algorithm as aes_algorithm
                            mode as mode
                            ciphertext as ciphertext_data
                            iv as empty list
                            tag as None
                            padding as PaddingScheme.PKCS7
                            metadata as empty dictionary
                        Return SymmetricSuccess with value as result
                    When SymmetricFailure:
                        Return ciphertext_result
            
            When BlockCipherMode.CBC:
                If (length of iv) is not equal to AES_BLOCK_SIZE:
                    Return SymmetricFailure with:
                        error as SymmetricError.Invalid_IV_Size
                        message as "AES-CBC requires 16-byte IV"
                
                Let ciphertext_result be aes_encrypt_cbc with plaintext as plaintext and key as key and iv as iv
                Match ciphertext_result:
                    When SymmetricSuccess with value as ciphertext_data:
                        Let result be SymmetricCiphertext with:
                            algorithm as aes_algorithm
                            mode as mode
                            ciphertext as ciphertext_data
                            iv as iv
                            tag as None
                            padding as PaddingScheme.PKCS7
                            metadata as empty dictionary
                        Return SymmetricSuccess with value as result
                    When SymmetricFailure:
                        Return ciphertext_result
            
            When BlockCipherMode.CTR:
                If (length of iv) is not equal to AES_BLOCK_SIZE:
                    Return SymmetricFailure with:
                        error as SymmetricError.Invalid_IV_Size
                        message as "AES-CTR requires 16-byte IV"
                
                Let ciphertext_result be aes_encrypt_ctr with plaintext as plaintext and key as key and iv as iv
                Match ciphertext_result:
                    When SymmetricSuccess with value as ciphertext_data:
                        Let result be SymmetricCiphertext with:
                            algorithm as aes_algorithm
                            mode as mode
                            ciphertext as ciphertext_data
                            iv as iv
                            tag as None
                            padding as PaddingScheme.No_Padding
                            metadata as empty dictionary
                        Return SymmetricSuccess with value as result
                    When SymmetricFailure:
                        Return ciphertext_result
            
            When BlockCipherMode.GCM:
                If (length of iv) is not equal to 12:
                    Return SymmetricFailure with:
                        error as SymmetricError.Invalid_IV_Size
                        message as "AES-GCM requires 12-byte IV"
                
                Let gcm_result be aes_encrypt_gcm with plaintext as plaintext and key as key and iv as iv and aad as empty list
                Match gcm_result:
                    When SymmetricSuccess with value as gcm_data:
                        Let result be SymmetricCiphertext with:
                            algorithm as aes_algorithm
                            mode as mode
                            ciphertext as gcm_data["ciphertext"]
                            iv as iv
                            tag as Some with value as gcm_data["tag"]
                            padding as PaddingScheme.No_Padding
                            metadata as dictionary containing: "aad" as empty list
                        Return SymmetricSuccess with value as result
                    When SymmetricFailure:
                        Return gcm_result
            
            Otherwise:
                Return SymmetricFailure with:
                    error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Mode
                    message as "Unsupported AES mode: " plus (mode as String)
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Encryption_Failed
            message as "AES encryption error: " plus error as String

Process called "aes_encrypt_cbc" that takes plaintext as List[Integer] and key as List[Integer] and iv as List[Integer] returns SymmetricResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: AES-CBC encryption implementation
    Try:
        Let ciphertext be empty list
        Let previous_block be iv
        
        Note: Process each 16-byte block
        For block_start from 0 to (length of plaintext minus AES_BLOCK_SIZE) by AES_BLOCK_SIZE:
            Let plaintext_block be plaintext from index block_start to (block_start plus AES_BLOCK_SIZE minus 1)
            
            Note: XOR with previous ciphertext block (or IV for first block)
            Let xor_block be xor_byte_arrays with array1 as plaintext_block and array2 as previous_block
            
            Note: Encrypt the XOR'd block
            Let encrypted_block_result be aes_encrypt_block with block as xor_block and key as key
            Match encrypted_block_result:
                When SymmetricFailure:
                    Return encrypted_block_result
                When SymmetricSuccess with value as encrypted_block:
                    Set ciphertext to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing ciphertext, encrypted_block
                    Set previous_block to encrypted_block
        
        Return SymmetricSuccess with value as ciphertext
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Encryption_Failed
            message as "AES-CBC encryption error: " plus error as String

Process called "aes_encrypt_block" that takes block as List[Integer] and key as List[Integer] returns SymmetricResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Encrypt single AES block using AES algorithm
    Try:
        Note: AES implementation with key expansion and rounds
        Let key_schedule_result be aes_key_expansion with key as key
        Match key_schedule_result:
            When SymmetricFailure:
                Return key_schedule_result
            When SymmetricSuccess with value as round_keys:
                Let state be block
                
                Note: Initial round key addition
                Set state to xor_byte_arrays with array1 as state and array2 as (round_keys at index 0)
                
                Note: Main rounds
                Let num_rounds be get_aes_rounds with key_size as (length of key)
                For round from 1 to (num_rounds minus 1):
                    Set state to aes_sub_bytes with state as state
                    Set state to aes_shift_rows with state as state
                    Set state to aes_mix_columns with state as state
                    Set state to xor_byte_arrays with array1 as state and array2 as (round_keys at index round)
                
                Note: Final round (no MixColumns)
                Set state to aes_sub_bytes with state as state
                Set state to aes_shift_rows with state as state
                Set state to xor_byte_arrays with array1 as state and array2 as (round_keys at index num_rounds)
                
                Return SymmetricSuccess with value as state
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Encryption_Failed
            message as "AES block encryption error: " plus error as String

Note: ChaCha20 Implementation

Process called "encrypt_chacha20" that takes plaintext as List[Integer] and key as List[Integer] and nonce as List[Integer] returns SymmetricResult[SymmetricCiphertext]:
    Note: ChaCha20 stream cipher encryption
    Try:
        Note: Validate ChaCha20 parameters
        If (length of key) is not equal to CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Key_Size
                message as "ChaCha20 requires 32-byte key"
        
        If (length of nonce) is not equal to CHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_IV_Size
                message as "ChaCha20 requires 12-byte nonce"
        
        Note: Initialize ChaCha20 state
        Let chacha_state_result be chacha20_initialize with key as key and nonce as nonce and counter as 0
        Match chacha_state_result:
            When SymmetricFailure:
                Return chacha_state_result
            When SymmetricSuccess with value as initial_state:
                Let ciphertext be empty list
                Let counter be 0
                
                Note: Process plaintext in 64-byte blocks
                For block_start from 0 to (length of plaintext minus 1) by 64:
                    Let block_size be minimum of 64 and ((length of plaintext) minus block_start)
                    Let plaintext_block be plaintext from index block_start to (block_start plus block_size minus 1)
                    
                    Note: Generate keystream block
                    Let keystream_result be chacha20_block with state as initial_state and counter as counter
                    Match keystream_result:
                        When SymmetricFailure:
                            Return keystream_result
                        When SymmetricSuccess with value as keystream:
                            Note: XOR plaintext with keystream
                            Let keystream_chunk be keystream from index 0 to (block_size minus 1)
                            Let ciphertext_block be xor_byte_arrays with array1 as plaintext_block and array2 as keystream_chunk
                            Set ciphertext to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing ciphertext, ciphertext_block
                            Set counter to counter plus 1
                
                Let result be SymmetricCiphertext with:
                    algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm.ChaCha20
                    mode as BlockCipherMode.CTR
                    ciphertext as ciphertext
                    iv as nonce
                    tag as None
                    padding as PaddingScheme.No_Padding
                    metadata as dictionary containing: "counter_start" as 0
                
                Return SymmetricSuccess with value as result
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Encryption_Failed
            message as "ChaCha20 encryption error: " plus error as String

Process called "chacha20_block" that takes state as List[Integer] and counter as Integer returns SymmetricResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Generate single ChaCha20 keystream block
    Try:
        Note: ChaCha20 quarter round function implementation
        Let working_state be state
        
        Note: Set counter in state (position 12)
        Set working_state at index 12 to counter
        
        Note: Perform 20 rounds (10 double rounds)
        For round from 0 to 9:
            Note: Odd round - column rounds
            Set working_state to chacha20_quarter_round with state as working_state and a as 0 and b as 4 and c as 8 and d as 12
            Set working_state to chacha20_quarter_round with state as working_state and a as 1 and b as 5 and c as 9 and d as 13
            Set working_state to chacha20_quarter_round with state as working_state and a as 2 and b as 6 and c as 10 and d as 14
            Set working_state to chacha20_quarter_round with state as working_state and a as 3 and b as 7 and c as 11 and d as 15
            
            Note: Even round - diagonal rounds
            Set working_state to chacha20_quarter_round with state as working_state and a as 0 and b as 5 and c as 10 and d as 15
            Set working_state to chacha20_quarter_round with state as working_state and a as 1 and b as 6 and c as 11 and d as 12
            Set working_state to chacha20_quarter_round with state as working_state and a as 2 and b as 7 and c as 8 and d as 13
            Set working_state to chacha20_quarter_round with state as working_state and a as 3 and b as 4 and c as 9 and d as 14
        
        Note: Add original state
        Let keystream be empty list
        For i from 0 to 15:
            Let sum be ((working_state at index i) plus (state at index i)) bitwise_and 4294967295
            Let sum_bytes be integer_to_bytes_little_endian with value as sum and byte_count as 4
            Set keystream to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing keystream, sum_bytes
        
        Return SymmetricSuccess with value as keystream
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
            message as "ChaCha20 block generation error: " plus error as String

Note: Padding Implementation

Process called "apply_padding" that takes data as List[Integer] and algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm and mode as BlockCipherMode and padding as PaddingScheme returns SymmetricResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Apply specified padding scheme to data
    Try:
        Note: Stream ciphers and certain modes don't require padding
        If mode is equal to BlockCipherMode.CTR or mode is equal to BlockCipherMode.GCM or algorithm is equal to SymmetricAlgorithm.ChaCha20 or algorithm is equal to SymmetricAlgorithm.XChaCha20:
            Return SymmetricSuccess with value as data
        
        If padding is equal to PaddingScheme.No_Padding:
            Return SymmetricSuccess with value as data
        
        Let block_size be get_block_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm
        If block_size is equal to 0:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Block_Size
                message as "Invalid block size for algorithm"
        
        Match padding:
            When PaddingScheme.PKCS7:
                Return apply_pkcs7_padding with data as data and block_size as block_size
            When PaddingScheme.ANSIX923:
                Return apply_ansix923_padding with data as data and block_size as block_size
            When PaddingScheme.ISO10126:
                Return apply_iso10126_padding with data as data and block_size as block_size
            When PaddingScheme.Zero_Padding:
                Return apply_zero_padding with data as data and block_size as block_size
            Otherwise:
                Return SymmetricFailure with:
                    error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Padding
                    message as "Unsupported padding scheme"
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
            message as "Padding application error: " plus error as String

Process called "apply_pkcs7_padding" that takes data as List[Integer] and block_size as Integer returns SymmetricResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Apply PKCS#7 padding
    Try:
        Let data_length be length of data
        Let padding_length be block_size minus (data_length modulo block_size)
        
        Note: PKCS#7 padding byte value equals padding length
        Let padded_data be data
        For i from 0 to (padding_length minus 1):
            Add padding_length to padded_data
        
        Return SymmetricSuccess with value as padded_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
            message as "PKCS#7 padding error: " plus error as String

Process called "remove_padding" that takes data as List[Integer] and padding as PaddingScheme returns SymmetricResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Remove specified padding from decrypted data
    Try:
        If padding is equal to PaddingScheme.No_Padding:
            Return SymmetricSuccess with value as data
        
        If (length of data) is equal to 0:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Ciphertext
                message as "Cannot remove padding from empty data"
        
        Match padding:
            When PaddingScheme.PKCS7:
                Return remove_pkcs7_padding with data as data
            When PaddingScheme.ANSIX923:
                Return remove_ansix923_padding with data as data
            When PaddingScheme.ISO10126:
                Return remove_iso10126_padding with data as data
            When PaddingScheme.Zero_Padding:
                Return remove_zero_padding with data as data
            Otherwise:
                Return SymmetricFailure with:
                    error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Padding
                    message as "Unsupported padding scheme for removal"
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
            message as "Padding removal error: " plus error as String

Process called "remove_pkcs7_padding" that takes data as List[Integer] returns SymmetricResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Remove PKCS#7 padding with validation
    Try:
        Let data_length be length of data
        If data_length is equal to 0:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Ciphertext
                message as "Empty data for padding removal"
        
        Let padding_length be data at index (data_length minus 1)
        If padding_length is equal to 0 or padding_length is greater than data_length:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Padding
                message as "Invalid PKCS#7 padding length"
        
        Note: Validate all padding bytes
        For i from (data_length minus padding_length) to (data_length minus 1):
            If (data at index i) is not equal to padding_length:
                Return SymmetricFailure with:
                    error as SymmetricError.Invalid_Padding
                    message as "Invalid PKCS#7 padding bytes"
        
        Let unpadded_data be data from index 0 to (data_length minus padding_length minus 1)
        Return SymmetricSuccess with value as unpadded_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
            message as "PKCS#7 padding removal error: " plus error as String

Note: Utility Functions

Process called "is_valid_key_for_algorithm" that takes key as SymmetricKey and algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate key compatibility with algorithm
    Try:
        If key.algorithm is not equal to algorithm:
            Return false
        
        Let expected_size be get_key_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm
        Return key.key_size is equal to expected_size
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "get_key_size_for_algorithm" that takes algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm returns Integer:
    Note: Get standard key size for algorithm
    Match algorithm:
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_128: Return 16
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_192: Return 24
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_256: Return 32
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.ChaCha20: Return 32
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.XChaCha20: Return 32
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.DES: Return 8
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.TripleDES: Return 24
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.Blowfish: Return 16
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.Twofish: Return 32
        Otherwise: Return 0

Process called "get_block_size_for_algorithm" that takes algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm returns Integer:
    Note: Get block size for block cipher algorithm
    Match algorithm:
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_128: Return 16
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_192: Return 16
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.AES_256: Return 16
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.DES: Return 8
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.TripleDES: Return 8
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.Blowfish: Return 8
        When SymmetricAlgorithm.Twofish: Return 16
        Otherwise: Return 0  Note: Stream ciphers have no block size

Process called "generate_iv_for_mode" that takes algorithm as SymmetricAlgorithm and mode as BlockCipherMode returns SymmetricResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Generate appropriate IV/nonce for algorithm and mode
    Try:
        Let iv_size be 0
        
        Match mode:
            When BlockCipherMode.ECB:
                Note: ECB doesn't use IV
                Return SymmetricSuccess with value as empty list
            When BlockCipherMode.CBC:
                Set iv_size to get_block_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm
            When BlockCipherMode.CFB:
                Set iv_size to get_block_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm
            When BlockCipherMode.OFB:
                Set iv_size to get_block_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm
            When BlockCipherMode.CTR:
                If algorithm is equal to SymmetricAlgorithm.ChaCha20:
                    Set iv_size to CHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE
                Else If algorithm is equal to SymmetricAlgorithm.XChaCha20:
                    Set iv_size to XCHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE
                Else:
                    Set iv_size to get_block_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm
            When BlockCipherMode.GCM:
                Set iv_size to 12  Note: Standard GCM nonce size
        
        If iv_size is equal to 0:
            Return SymmetricFailure with:
                error as SymmetricError.Invalid_IV_Size
                message as "Cannot determine IV size for algorithm/mode combination"
        
        Let iv_result be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as iv_size
        Match iv_result:
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as iv:
                Return SymmetricSuccess with value as iv
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return SymmetricFailure with:
                    error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
                    message as "Failed to generate IV"
    
    Catch error:
        Return SymmetricFailure with:
            error as SymmetricError.Internal_Error
            message as "IV generation error: " plus error as String

Process called "xor_byte_arrays" that takes array1 as List[Integer] and array2 as List[Integer] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: XOR two byte arrays element-wise
    Let result be empty list
    Let min_length be minimum of (length of array1) and (length of array2)
    
    For i from 0 to (min_length minus 1):
        Add (array1 at index i bitwise_xor array2 at index i) to result
    
    Return result

Process called "concatenate_byte_arrays" that takes arrays as List[List[Integer]] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Concatenate multiple byte arrays
    Let result be empty list
    For array in arrays:
        For byte in array:
            Add byte to result
    Return result

Process called "integer_to_bytes_little_endian" that takes value as Integer and byte_count as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Convert integer to little-endian byte array
    Let bytes be empty list
    Let temp_value be value
    
    For i from 0 to (byte_count minus 1):
        Add (temp_value bitwise_and 255) to bytes
        Set temp_value to temp_value right_shift 8
    
    Return bytes

Process called "minimum" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
        Return a
    Else:
        Return b

Process called "maximum" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
        Return a
    Else:
        Return b